-- Yen Falls Versus Euro on Signs Global Economic Recovery Gaining Traction
-- Ronnie Harui
-- 2010-06-13T23:10:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/yen-falls-versus-euro-on-signs-global-economic-recovery-gaining-traction.html

          
          
             The yen fell as signs the global
economic recovery is gaining traction reduced demand for Japan’s
currency as a refuge.  
 The yen weakened to 111.66 per euro as of 8:07 a.m. in
Tokyo from 111 in New York on June 11. It slipped to 78.31
against the Australian dollar from 77.94.  
 Europe’s shared currency rose to as high as $1.2194, the
highest level since June 4, from $1.2112 in New York.  
